the 1989 Revolution. It was a moment we were all sure to remember with specificity. It was a moment when the unity of the nation, which was simply long lost, reappeared. The goal of “Romanian Revolution – 30 Years Later” exhibition is to create a transgenerational memory space in which one can understand almost without words what happened this day at the Palace of Parliament. Everyone who went to that day had a role, many were passive contributors, others involved like actors, many were like nurses who helped the wounded. I think the importance of their contribution, their story, their truth is fundamental for these 30 years to come.

CadouriTourist
